<Body NumberFormat="default">
<P1group id="p00003">
<Title><?start-line?>Child maltreatment</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Section 1 of the Children and Young Persons Act 1933 is amended as follows.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>For subsection (1) substitute—</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<BlockAmendment TargetClass="primary" Context="main" TargetSubClass="unknown" Format="double">
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>If a person who has attained the age of 16 years with responsibility for <?new-line?>a child intentionally or recklessly subjects that child or allows that child <?new-line?>to be subjected to maltreatment, whether by act or omission, such that <?new-line?>the child suffers, or is likely to suffer, significant harm, that person shall <?new-line?>be guilty of an offence, and shall be liable—</Text>
<P3>
<Pnumber>a</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>on conviction on indictment, to a fine or alternatively, or in <?new-line?>addition thereto, to imprisonment for any term not exceeding <?new-line?>ten years;</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
<P3>
<Pnumber>b</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>on summary conviction, to a fine not exceeding £3,500 or <?new-line?>alternatively, or in addition thereto, to imprisonment for any <?new-line?>term not exceeding six months.</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
</P2para>
</P2>
</BlockAmendment>
<P2>
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>For subsection (2) substitute—</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<BlockAmendment TargetClass="primary" Context="main" TargetSubClass="unknown" Format="double">
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>For the purposes of this section—</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<UnorderedList Decoration="none" Class="Definition">
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>“harm” means the impairment of—</Text>
<OrderedList Decoration="parens" Type="alpha">
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>physical or mental health, or</Text>
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>physical, intellectual, emotional, social or behavioural <?new-line?>development;</Text>
</Para>
</ListItem>
</OrderedList>
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>“recklessly” shall mean that a person with responsibility for a <?new-line?>child foresaw a risk that an act or omission regarding that child <?new-line?>would be likely to result in significant harm, but nonetheless <?new-line?>unreasonably took that risk;</Text>
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>“maltreatment” includes—</Text>
<?new-page?><OrderedList Decoration="parens" Type="alpha">
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>neglect (including abandonment),</Text>
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>physical abuse,</Text>
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>sexual abuse,</Text>
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>exploitation, and</Text>
</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>
<Text><?start-line?>emotional abuse.</Text>
</Para>
</ListItem>
</OrderedList>
</Para>
</ListItem>
</UnorderedList>
</BlockAmendment>
<P2>
<Pnumber>4</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>After subsection (3) insert—</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<BlockAmendment TargetClass="primary" Context="main" TargetSubClass="unknown" Format="double">
<P2>
<Pnumber>3A</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>Where the question of whether harm suffered by a child is significant <?new-line?>turns on the child’s health or development, that child’s health or <?new-line?>development shall be compared with that which could reasonably be <?new-line?>expected of a similar child.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</BlockAmendment>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
<P1group id="p00005">
<Title><?start-line?>Short title, commencement and extent</Title>
<P1>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2>
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act may be cited as the Child Maltreatment Act 2013.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act extends to England and Wales only.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This Act comes into force two months after Royal Assent.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1>
</P1group>
